AINING LIBRARY ASSISTANTS IN MAURITIUS.THE UNIVERSITY OF MAURITIUS WITH THE FINANCIAL HELP OF THE INTERNATIONALDEVELOPMENT RESEARCH CENTRE OF CANADA (IDRC) EMBARKED ON A 15 MONTHEXPERIMENTAL COURSE IN 1978 FOR THE TRAINING OF LIBRARY ASSISTANTS WHO WEREALREADY WORKING IN LIBRARIES. THE MAIN AIM OF THE EXPERIMENT WAS TO EVOLVE ACOURSE OF APPROXIMATELY 1 YEAR TAKING 3 AFTERNOONS WEEKLY, GEARED TO LOCALCONDITIONS AND USING AVAILABLE RESOURCES. THE EXPERIMENT WAS A SUCCESS AND THECOURSE, AFTER MINOR ALTERATIONS, WAS CONTINUED IN 1981